content.rendered:
Natalie and Tyler's elegant fall wedding ceremony and reception at The Bell Tower was a night of true black tie elegance paired with the couple's electric love and fun spirit.

The couple's theme was a gorgeous midnight blue and black. A black sequined linen was custom-made for their cake table, and Ashley Walters of Forget Me Not Flower Shop designed arrangements of lush greenery and ivory flowers.

Natalie, the fabulous bride herself, designed all of the amazing signs, menus, tags and everything for their special day.

And the couple's electric love and fun spirit was contagious. As can be seen throughout the photos captured that night. Congratulations to Natalie and Tyler!

WEDDING DETAILS

Date: October 7, 2016
Bride & Groom: Natalie and Tyler
Location: The Bell Tower
Guest Count: 91
Colors: Midnight Blue & Black
Photographer: Krista Lee Photography
Florist: Forget Me Not Designs
Cake: Dulce Desserts
Paper Goods: The Bride!
DJ/Band: DJ Rich
Catering: The Bell Tower
Production: Infinity Hospitality
Planning: Lesa | IH
